<subSubSection id="02C66578FFF9FFB8FC959AA26DF17A1E" pageId="20" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF9FFB8FC959AA26C627A5E" blockId="20.[831,1437,1766,1919]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FC959AA26ABD7B9F" bold="true" box="[831,944,1766,1790]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is distinguished by having an umbo. It is worth mentioning that SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956) considered 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFF9FFB8FC109B636D037A5E" box="[954,1038,1831,1855]" class="Nodosariata" family="Vaginulinidae" genus="Robulus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaginulinida" pageId="20" pageNumber="34" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="isidis">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FC109B636D037A5E" box="[954,1038,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">L. isidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFF9FFB8FBE89B636DEB7A5E" baseAuthorityName="CUSHMAN" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[1090,1254,1831,1855]" class="Globothalamea" family="Tritaxiidae" genus="Tritaxia" kingdom="Chromista" order="Lituolida" pageId="20" pageNumber="34" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="midwayensis">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FBE89B636DEB7A5E" box="[1090,1254,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">L. midwayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
one species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF9FFB8FC959B036DF17A1E" blockId="20.[831,1437,1766,1919]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FC959B036D707A3E" bold="true" box="[831,1149,1863,1887]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
